{"file":"src/cx/scope.rs","lines":3500,"batch":"qg5th0-fix","date":"2026-05-07","agent":"SapphireHill","verdict":"FIXED","bugs":2,"notes":"qg5th0 root cause: (1) panic-rollback orphan filter at scope.rs:917 matched only TaskState::Created, but cancel_request at line 906 transitions tasks to CancelRequested before the filter runs, so orphans were missed and never recycled — leaving region.task_count() > 0 and blocking advance_region_state. Fix: match Created|CancelRequested. (2) Three async-spawn wrappers delivered results via tx.send(&cx_for_send, ...) where cx_for_send is the task's OWN cancellable Cx; when a task explicitly observed cancellation via cx.checkpoint() and returned its cancellation-aware payload (e.g. \"cancelled\"), the post-completion delivery failed with SendError::Cancelled and TaskHandle::join saw the channel close instead of the value. Fix: use tx.send_blocking(...) (no Cx, immediate, never cancellable). All 3 wrapper sites converted (lines ~457/463, ~696/703, ~830/836). Bundled into c8b8723c2 by another agent. cx::scope::tests now 42/42 pass (was 38/42)."}
